definition.value: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is 5-chloro-10-hydroxy-8-methyl-1H-oxepino[4,3-b]chromene-3,11-dione which is substituted at positions 1, 5, 8, and 10 by methoxycarbonyl, chlorine, methyl, and hydroxy groups, respectively (the 1S enantiomer). Found in Monilia fructicola and in the mycoherbicide Alternaria sonchi.
An  ergostanoid that is the methyl ester of zhankuic acid A. It has been isolated from the fruiting bodies of  Taiwanofungus camphoratus.
A tetracyclic triterpenoid that is 24,25-dihydrolanosterol carrying an additional methylene substituent at position 24. A natural product found in Taiwanofungus camphoratus.
A  resin glycoside that is the  tetrasaccharide derivative of jalapinolic acid. Isolated from Ipomoea batatas, it exhibits inhibitory activity against COX-1 and COX-2.
A resin glycoside that is the tetrasaccharide derivative of jalapinolic acid. It has been isolated from Ipomoea batatas.
